# Decide Claude auto-memory

## Step

Claude Code's auto-memory (`~/.claude/projects/-Users-joel/memory/`) is a
live shadow source: it duplicates operator truths that belong in the
Brain, and it wrote a fresh topic page on 07-17 after Joel's 07-16
Brain-only instruction. Settle: disable topic-page writes entirely, or
reshape the surface into a read-only index pointing at Brain pages —
and either way, what happens to the 18 existing topic pages (migrate the
non-duplicated facts into Brain `.svx`, then delete?). The answer must
bind future Claude sessions mechanically (instruction text where the
memory feature reads it), not aspirationally. Evidence:
[periphery survey](../memory-system-review/periphery-survey.svx)
"Claude auto-memory".
